FBIS4-16146 "drsov072_e_94007" FBIS-SOV-94-072 Daily Report 13 Apr 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs Black Sea Ships `Prepared for Military Action' Black Sea Ships `Prepared for Military Action' LD1304210194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1835 GMT 13 Apr 94 LD1304210194 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] The Black Sea Fleet ships stationed in Sevastopol, for instance the Admiral Golovko rocket cruiser, are being urgently supplied with armaments. This was announced to INTERFAX-Ukraine by Chief of the Ukrainian Navy press center, Nikolay Savchenko. He said the ships were prepared for military action. Savchenko also announced that several Ukrainian fleet ships, for instance the Getman Sagaidachny patrol ship and the Lutsk antisubmarine cruiser had not been supplied with electric power from the land. The Black See Fleet's command explained this by nonpayment for electric power already delivered. However, the Ukrainian Navy financial service said Kiev had no debts.
